  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective observational registry study tracking hemolysis indices across clinical CPB cases, which the assessment narrative describes as functionally equivalent to controlled experimental validation. The observational dataset covers 5 flow-speed combinations and yields relative hemolysis index values compared against a predicate device benchmark (RH < 1). The assessment team concluded that the breadth and consistency of the registry data provide confidence comparable to a controlled experiment, citing low inter-case variability and standardised measurement protocols as justification for treating the observational cohort as a controlled-experiment surrogate.",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
