      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Comparison — CPB Registry Cohort",
      "description": "Predicted RH values from the CFD model were compared against measured hemolysis indices drawn from a prospective observational registry of 47 CPB procedures. All 5 flow-speed operating points yielded RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. Inter-case coefficient of variation was 6.3%, supporting the assessment team's conclusion that registry conditions were sufficiently uniform to serve as a controlled reference. The activity is described throughout the assessment report as 'controlled experimental validation' owing to the standardised clinical protocol, but the underlying data collection was conducted without experimental manipulation of independent variables.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-registry-data-collection",
