    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. The validation evidence, drawn from a 47-case CPB registry cohort, demonstrates that predicted RH values are within ±12% of measured values across all five operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. The assessment team concluded that the registry data, collected under standardised clinical protocols with low inter-case variability, provide credibility evidence functionally equivalent to controlled experimental validation. Six factors were not assessed, consistent with ASME V&V 40 requirements at MRL 2. The UoA is accepted for use in the Class II CPB device submission.",
